column5: What is the ice situation North of 11 near Long Lac, Geraldton, Nakina?

Ice has some thickness yet from my last report. There is easily over 24" of ice, but it is not good ice. There is a lot of slush this year, plus with early snow just after the ice started to form there is a good amount of honeycomb to it. With an average amount of warmth, I would predict the last couple days of April, or the first couple days of May for ice-out. Agate
